<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="296" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1506,1963]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1866,1891]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was originally described from an unknown number of specimens from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1313,1432,1866,1891]" name="Singapore" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Singapore</collectingCountry>
, Panang’. It can be distinguished from other species of the genus by the large yellow spot next to the eye on the vertex and distinctive shape of the aedeagus (see above).
</paragraph>
